&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In my infrastructure, I have two Git repositories. The first one, &amp;ldquo;personal_website,&amp;rdquo; contains all the Hugo code required to build the site. The second one, &amp;ldquo;Pamilator.github.io,&amp;rdquo; receives the &amp;ldquo;public&amp;rdquo; folder generated during the build, which represents the actual website. I deliberately separated the code from the result, and for now, it&amp;rsquo;s sufficient for my needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Feel free to check out my repositories:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/Pamilator/Pamilator.github.io&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Pamilator.github.io&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
